Key Match Events: Heston Kjerstad went deep to launch the Baltimore Orioles into the postseason
Cristian Santana homered to right center (393 feet) in the 2nd inning
Drew Keirsey Jr. homered to right (368 feet) in the 3rd inning
James McCann homered to left (381 feet), O'Hearn scored and Mullins scored in the 5th inning
Jared Westburg singled to left, Mullins scored and O'Hearn scored, Holliday to third in the 7th inning
Heston Kjerstad homered to center (414 feet) in the 8th inning
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles power into the playoffs on HRs by McCann, Kjerstad for 6-2 win to finish sweep of Twins
The game finished with a 6-2 victory for the Orioles
